Tik Tok Toe

by: Graham

This game was made for my level 2 project at The League of Amazing Programmers.
Click here to download and play!

1. Why I Made This Game

I decided to make this game because I wanted to make a simple game that wouldn't take took much time. There were other games that I would have considered and originally I did a different game but because it was taking too long and I was spending too much time in this unit, I ended up making this game.

2. What I Learned

I learnt that there were a few bugs in the game. I quickly fixed them and added some suggested features such as randomized memes.

3. Architecture of My Game

In this game there are only a few classes, there's a Startup class for creating the JFrame, there is a Main class which runs most of the code. There's a computer class which is for calculating the next move. The classes interact by first creating the frame. After that, the Main Class runs all of the frame draws and updates everything. When needed the Main Class will call Methods from the Computer class to calculate the computers move.

4. Technical Implementation

My favorite part of the game is probably the random memes. I did this by creating a table of strings which hold urls for memes. When the user wants to get a meme, they click the 'wak yo toe' button and it will give some dialog and then redirect the user to a website which displays a meme.

5. Most Challenging Part

The most challenging party of the project was bug fixing. The reason why it was difficult was because its really boring to figure out what exactly is happening so I would have to read through all the code just to figure it out. Once I did that, I had no idea on how to fix it so I would sometimes re-write large chunks of code to just fix one problem.

6. Future Fixes and Updates

In the future, I would give multiple more features such as the ability to choose the difficulty level of the computer. Another thing I would do is add a fully randomly generated meme every time you wack your toe which makes it unique.
